类 ViewModelProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.agilelink.framework.ViewModelProvider
  • 所有已实现的接口:

    直接已知子类:
    AMAPViewModelProvider

    public class ViewModelProvider
extends java.lang.Object
implements AylaSystemSettings.DeviceDetailProvider
    The ViewModelProvider object is responsible for providing the framework with a set of models that are used by the AMAP framework to provide device-specific information to the UI engine. The Agile Link framework requests a ViewModel for a particular device when it needs information to construct the UI or gain additional device-specific information. Agile Link application implementers should always override the ViewModelProvider object and assign an instance of it to the AMAPCore.SessionParameters.viewModelProvider variable. When the framework needs additional information about an AylaDevice, it will call viewModelForDevice(com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaDevice) method to obtain a ViewModel for the specified device. If an unknown device is encountered, the ViewModelProvider may return null to indicate that the device should not be presented to the user, or it may return a generic ViewModel object

      • viewModelForDevice

        public ViewModel viewModelForDevice(AylaDevice aylaDevice)
        Returns a Device object for the supplied AylaDevice object. Derived classes should override this method to return a Device-derived object specific to the application.
        参数:
        aylaDevice - The AylaDevice object to be wrapped
        返回:
        a Device-derived object wrapping the supplied AylaDevice

      • getManagedPropertyNames

        public java.lang.String[] getManagedPropertyNames(AylaDevice device)
        指定者:
        getManagedPropertyNames 在接口中 AylaSystemSettings.DeviceDetailProvider
        参数:
        device - the AylaDevice that is requesting the names of managed properties
        返回:
        an array of property names (Strings) that the DeviceManager should keep up-to-date. If this method returns null for a given device, all properties will be fetched for that device.
